The art is nice, but seems to lack detail. Her armour, particularly her shoulder guards, look like they're made of styrofoam. And the card is ridiculously shiny. It's a little surreal.  

That being said, I love the cloak and her stance. I'm glad I bought one of the duel decks. It's like I actually paid 25 dollars for an Elspeth, and they threw in a Tezzeret and a bunch of other cards.  

@Richard\_Hawk A poor man's Tirel? Are you out of your mind? Even this version is $17.50. A foil Shards one is 50. I wouldn't say that this version is inferior to Tirel, either.

Another Planeswalker with an Emblem ability has been previewed. [Koth of the Hammer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Koth of the Hammer).


@theelk801, [Venser](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Venser) doesn't have an Emblem ability.


